title: Football: Toms River South rallies around Jaden Kosh for victory
text:
MORE STAFFORD — Toms River South senior Jaden Kosh left the game in the fourth quarter with a knee injury but the starting quarterback had already made his mark on the game at that point.
With Kosh ruled out for the remainder of Saturday’s game, the Indians rallied around their leader and eventually scored another touchdown to put the finishing touches on a 21-0 Class A South victory over host Southern.
“I took a helmet to the knee and hopefully I’ll be back soon,” said Kosh after the game with his left knee wrapped with ice. “I was a little nervous about coming out of the game and I was hoping my teammates didn’t get down about it.”
When Kosh got injured with 9:33 left in the fourth quarter, he had just scored on a 10-yard run. Senior kicker Tyler Sosa then added the extra point and the Indians (4-1, 3-1) held a 14-0 lead after that sequence.
